{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Make the BBC a fully-mutual body based on licence-fee payers",
        "additional_details": "The BBC is intended to be politically neutral but we are concerned that in practice the Government is able to exert political pressure through the Charter Renewal process, the appointment of Board Members, and other forms of suasion.\r\n \r\nWe think a governance structure which derives its authority direct from licence-fee payers will truly be able to 'speak truth to power' and play a vital function in generating genuine debate in national affairs, in contrast to the monochrome politics of the print media.",
        "background": "The BBC Charter review must consider the option of creating a fully-mutual BBC based on licence-fee payers (or those excepted by statute), with all non-executive positions elected (by PR) by members at large.",
